annotationA: GTP-binding protein Rheb homolog; Binds GTP and exhibits intrinsic GTPase activity (By similarity). Activates the protein kinase activity of TORC1, and thereby plays a role in the regulation of apoptosis. Stimulates the phosphorylation of S6K through activation of TORC1 signaling. May also have a role in activating TORC2 signaling
annotationB: CG6182; Rab GTPase activator activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: regulation of Rab GTPase activity
